posts.title: Update on Nephew that was killed in a hit and run last week
posts.content:
Previous post: https://patriots.win/p/17txMS4z8p/nephew-killed-in-a-hit-and-run-p/c

His funeral was yesterday and, as expected, it was pretty emotional day for my family made even more emotional after seeing his friends from school that came from far and wide to celebrate his life.

I learned from my sister that the police do indeed have a suspect and have issued warrants. They want to keep this information low key. I'm just glad to hear there are warrants out. I won't feel ok about any of this until that person is caught and punished for they did to my family.

My sister seems to be doing ok. She has a 5 month old grandchild that she baby sits often and I think he keeps her from slipping into depression and keeps her busy. My brother in law is angry. He's ready for results. He's the type that won't rest until there is some form of restitution either by the law or other means.

Thank you all so much for your prayers and words of comfort last week. I do want to say I learned that my nephew had become a Trump supporter late in the game... but he did come around at the point when all of the Trump supporters had been called all kinds of disparaging things along the lines of "basket of deplorables". All the personal attacks against Trump supporters turned him into a Trump supporter.

He had also spent the last several years struggling with drug addiction. He was finally getting clean it seemed. He had started studying the Bible. He made his last post on social media the day before he died and said this: If I die tomorrow, I'll be with the Lord. If I live tomorrow the Lord will be with me. Either way, I belong to him. And I can never thank him enough for staying by my side through thick and thin.

I've also learned he had been talking with other Christians he knew that were helping him as he was raised in an agnostic (maybe even atheist) environment and was new to Christ. I take comfort in the fact that he knew the Lord.

Thank you all for your comments last week. You made a dark week a little brighter for me.
